on Margaret Sullavan: "Well, I really wouldn't care to scratch your surface, Mr. Crawley.  Because I know exactly what I'd find. Instead of a heart, a handbag. Instead of a soul, a suitcase. Instead of an intellect, a cigarette lighter...which doesn't work."~ ~
on James Stewart: "You know, people seldom go to the trouble of scratching the surface of things to find the inner truth."~ ~
